'''OpenView Venture Partners''' is an American [[venture capital]] firm based in [[Boston]]. The organization provides expansion-stage software and technology companies around the world with operational support.<ref>{{cite web|author=Wednesday, May 15th, 2012 |url=http://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2011/04/19/openview-thrives-on-full-service-philosophy/ |title=OpenView Thrives on a Full Service Approach |publisher=WSJ |date=2011-04-19 |accessdate=2012-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Wednesday, May 22th, 2012 |url=http://www.boston.com/business/technology/innoeco/2011/08/inside_openviews_corporate_rel.html |title=Inside OpenView's corporate relocation program |publisher=Boston Globe |date=2011-08-02 |accessdate=2012-05-23}}</ref> They have launched three funds since the company was established in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|author=Wednesday, May 15th, 2012 |url=http://www.crunchbase.com/financial-organization/openview-venture-partners |title=OpenView Venture Partners Crunchbase |publisher=Crunchbase |date=2012-05-16 |accessdate=2012-05-16}}</ref>  Scott Maxwell founded the firm.  The firm's venture partners include Firas Raouf and George Roberts, former EVP of North American Sales at Oracle. 

OpenView provides capital to a range of dynamic companies, including [[AtTask]], Balihoo, [[Central Desktop]], [[Exinda]], Intronis, [[Instructure]], Kareo, Loyalty Lab (acquired by [[Tibco]]), Mashery, Monetate, NextDocs, [[Open-e]], Prognosis Health Information Systems, Reality Digital, [[Skytap]], Sonian, UnboundID, uSamp, VersionOne, and Zmags.<ref>{{cite web|author=Wednesday, May 15th, 2012 |url=http://www.crunchbase.com/financial-organization/openview-venture-partners |title=OpenView Venture Partners Crunchbase |publisher=Crunchbase |date=2012-05-16 |accessdate=2012-05-16}}</ref> The firm announced its third fund totaling $200 million in March 2012,<ref>{{cite web|author=Wednesday, March 21st, 2012 |url=http://techcrunch.com/2012/03/21/more-money-for-big-data-and-the-cloud-openview-raises-new-200m-fund/ |title=More Money For Big Data And The Cloud: OpenView Raises New $200M Fund |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2012-03-21 |accessdate=2012-05-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Tuesday, May 23rd, 2012 |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/blog/startups/2012/03/bostons-openview-venture-capital.html |title=Boston's OpenView Venture Partners closes 3rd VC fund at $200M |publisher=Boston Business Journal |date=2012-03-21 |accessdate=2012-05-23}}</ref> and was recently named one of the top 10 venture capital brands by Heardable.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bernhard |first=Kent |url=http://www.portfolio.com/views/blogs/money-hunt/2012/03/20/fred-wilson-tops-heardable-venture-capital-rank |title=Fred Wilson Tops Heardable Venture Capital Rank - Loot |publisher=Portfolio.com |date=2012-03-20 |accessdate=2012-05-11}}</ref>

OpenView Venture Partners also employs a wide network of senior advisors including [[Jeff Sutherland]] among others.

==The firm==
OpenView is a venture capital firm specializing in expansion stage software, new media, Internet, and technology enabled companies.  Expansion stage companies have a solid growth rate and achieving $500,000 to $5,000,000 in quarterly sales.  The firm seeks to invest in companies that are located anywhere in the world and have a strategy of dominating the North American market.  The firm typically invests $5 to $15 million in growth capital.  The firm specializes in offering value-add assistance to its portfolio companies, focusing on the areas of recruiting/onboarding, decision support, and go to market strategy.

